description: Zod schema conventions — trim before min, UUID IDs, export inferred types
globs: packages/shared/**/*.ts
alwaysApply: false
---

# Zod Schema Rules

## Always trim before min on strings
```typescript
// ❌ BAD — passes whitespace-only strings like "   "
z.string().min(1)

// ✅ GOOD
z.string().trim().min(1).max(200)
```

## All ID fields must be validated as UUIDs
```typescript
// ❌ BAD
laneId: z.string()

// ✅ GOOD
laneId: z.string().uuid()
```

## Position fields must be non-negative integers
```typescript
position: z.number().int().min(0)
```

## Always export both the schema and the inferred type
```typescript
export const createCardSchema = z.object({
  title: z.string().trim().min(1).max(200),
  description: z.string().trim().optional(),
  laneId: z.string().uuid(),
});

export type CreateCardDto = z.infer<typeof createCardSchema>;
```

## Schema file per domain
- `schemas/auth.ts` — register, login, refresh
- `schemas/board.ts` — createBoard, updateBoard
- `schemas/lane.ts` — createLane, updateLane, reorderLanes
- `schemas/card.ts` — createCard, updateCard, moveCard

All schemas are re-exported from `packages/shared/index.ts`.
